History of operating systems.

Functions of old operating systems which run on mainframes.
Terminals, vt100.

Terminal emulators: xterm.
Terminal device files: /dev/pts/* /dev/tty*

Sending message from one terminal to the other by writing in to device files by identifying the other terminal with 'w' and writing with 'echo'.

DOS, Windows 9x, Windows NT evolution, in particular:
* memory models: segmented vs flat.
* task switchers: co-operative task switcher vs pre-emptive multitasking(meaning your machine wouldn't lock up due to busy loops, and would have to find new 32 bit ways to lock up instead.


